com.guille.ed.graphs

Class Graph<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.guille.ed.graphs.Graph<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Type of data stored in the graph.

    public class Graph<T extends java.lang.Comparable<T>>
extends java.lang.Object
    Simulates a graph by creating nodes, edges and some methods like Floyd and Dijkstra.
    Version:
    2.1
    Author:
    Guillermo Facundo Colunga

      • getA

        Returns:
        Floyd's A matrix

      • getP

        public int[][] getP()
        Returns matrix P from Floyd's algorithm. Contains the previous node that must be visited to get to any node from any other node.
        Returns:
        Floyd's P matrix

      • floyd

        public void floyd(int An)
        Executes the algorithm. Calculates the weight of going from each node to all the others making a stop through a different node each time. If it's less than the direct value, the A matrix is updated and the intermediate node is written in the P matrix.

      • printFloydPath

        public java.lang.String printFloydPath(T departure,
                                       T destination)
        Returns an String containing the path with the minimum cost to get from one node to a different one using Floyd's algorithm. Notice that my algorithm return the hole path from the departure to the destination both of them included. If not, then for a direct connection would return an empty String
        Parameters:
        departure - node to start floyd
        destination - node to end floyd
        Returns:
        string describing the minimum cost path.

      • getD

        public double[][] getD()
        Returns matrix D from Dijkstra's algorithm. Contains the minimum cost of going to any node from the node the algorithm has been executed over. We're doing it in that way because the assertArrayEqualsTo has a bug for double[].
        Returns:
        Dijkstra's D matrix.

      • getPD

        public int[] getPD()
        Returns matrix P from Dijkstra's algorithm. Contains the previous node that must be visited to get to any node from the node the algorithm has been executed over.
        Returns:
        Dijkstra's P matrix

      • Dijkstra

        public void Dijkstra(T departureNode)
        Complexity --> O(n2) Quadratic implementation for the Dijkstra algorithm. This algorithm calculates the shortest path from a source node to every other nodes in the graph.

      • getNumberOfReturnNodesWithinCost

        public int getNumberOfReturnNodesWithinCost(T source,
                                            double cost)
                                     throws java.lang.Exception
        It return the number of nodes n such that is possible to go from the source to them and return to the source with no more cost than the one provided.
        Parameters:
        source - the node where we start the algorithm and therefore the path
        cost. - The maximum possible cost to reach and return any nodes from the source.
        Returns:
        the number of reachable nodes within the range of cost.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - if the cost provided is negative. Cost must be always positive.

      • isStronglyConnected

        public boolean isStronglyConnected(T node)
        IMPLEMENTING FLOYD Checks whether a node is strongly connected, i.e. there is a path from the node to every other node in the graph and at the same time from every other node to it.
        Parameters:
        node - Node to check
        Returns:
        whether the node is strongly connected
